The paper deals with the problem of adversarial robustness in machine learning models, specifically boosted decision trees and decision stumps. This falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of the algorithms used, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of the ensemble, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
